Boda boda riders from Athi River subcounty have been banned from operating late in the night. Deputy county commissioner Geoffrey Omoding said the ban will reduce crime.He spoke at Mlolongo town during a security meeting with boda boda operators and the subcounty security team on Tuesday. Omoding said no rider should operate their business after 11pm.Omoding said residents and businessmen have been attacked, robbed and killed by bandits on motorbikes. They are suspected of colluding with some boda boda operators who offer getaway transport. He said the ban will also protect operators who have fallen victims.